reports.query:
**Welcome to MASS dashboard**

Data source: monitoringresource.org

A graphical dashboard of programs, protocols, and methods

reports.title: MASS database sample overview
Select an program to view details
reports.query:
MATCH (n:`Programs`) 
WHERE toLower(toString(n.`name`)) CONTAINS toLower($input) 
RETURN DISTINCT n.`name` as value,  n.`name` as display ORDER BY size(toString(value)) ASC LIMIT 5

reports.title: Details of selected programs
reports.query:
MATCH (p: Programs)
WHERE p.name = $neodash_programs_name_01
UNWIND keys(p) as pk 
WITH p, pk
RETURN pk as Properties, p[pk] as values ORDER BY pk

reports.title: Statistic summary
reports.query:
CALL apoc.meta.stats() YIELD labels
RETURN labels.Organizations as Total_Organizations, labels.Programs as Total_Programs, labels.Protocols as total_Protocols, labels.Methods as Total_Methods

reports.title: Protocol's connections
reports.query:
MATCH path = (p:Protocols {title: $neodash_protocols_title_01})--()
RETURN path

reports.title: Method's connections

RETURN path

reports.title: Programs connections between 1 and 2
reports.query:
MATCH (o1:Organizations {uid: $neodash_organizations_uid_01}) 
WITH o1
MATCH (o2: Organizations {uid: $neodash_organizations_uid_02})
WITH o1, o2
MATCH p = ((o1)-->()<--(o2))
RETURN p

reports.title: Total connected programs
reports.query:
MATCH (o1:Organizations {uid: $neodash_organizations_uid_01}) 
WITH o1
MATCH (o2: Organizations {uid: $neodash_organizations_uid_02})
WITH o1, o2
MATCH p = ((o1)-->()<--(o2))
RETURN COUNT(NODES(p)) as Total_programs_connected

reports.title: Shortest connections path between methods
reports.query:
MATCH (m1: Methods {title: $neodash_methods_title_02}) 
WITH m1
MATCH (m2: Methods {title: $neodash_methods_title_03})
WITH m1, m2
MATCH p = SHORTESTPATH((m1)-[*]-(m2))
RETURN p

reports.title: Total steps to reach other method
reports.query:
MATCH (m1: Methods {title: $neodash_methods_title_02}) 
WITH m1
MATCH (m2: Methods {title: $neodash_methods_title_03})
WITH m1, m2
MATCH p = SHORTESTPATH((m1)-[*]-(m2))
RETURN SIZE(NODES(p))-2 as Total_steps
